parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The steering vibration and drift can cause the vehicle to lose directional control, making it difficult to steer, which can lead to accidents or loss of control, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The steering wheel vibrates or shakes
the vehicle drifts into another lane
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the vehicle requires both hands to make small corrections
the vehicle is impossible to drive with one hand
the vibration is more pronounced at high speeds (65 mph and up).
